definition.value: A decenoic acid having the double bond at position 9.
A mandelate that is the conjugate base of (R)-mandelic acid.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion and the conjugate base of 6-hydroxyhexanoic acid, formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.

A straight-chain polyunsaturated fatty acid comprising tridecanoic acid having (E)- and (Z)-double bonds at positions 3 and 5 respectively, an allenic system at positions 7-9 and triple bonds at positions 10 and 12.
A linolenate that is the conjugate base of alpha-linolenic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
An octadecatetraenoic acid having four double bonds located at positions 6, 9, 12 and 15 (the all-cis-isomer). It has been isolated from Lithospermum officinale and fish oils.
A linolenate that is the conjugate base of gamma-linolenic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
A tetracosenoate that is the conjugate base of nervonic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
A unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of erucic acid, formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
A long-chain fatty acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxy group of arachidonic acid.
An amino-acid anion that is the conjugate base of 6-aminohexanoic acid.
A crown ether that is cyclooctadecane in which the carbon atoms at positions 1, 4, 7, 10, 13 and 16 have been replaced by oxygen atoms.
The D-enantiomer of glyceric acid.
A crown ether that is cyclododecane in which the carbon atoms at positions 1, 4, 7 and 10 have been replaced by oxygen atoms.

A member of the class of imidazoles that is 1H-imidazole in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is substituted by a 4-(4-chlorophenyl)-2-[(2,6-dichlorophenyl)sulfanyl]butyl group. An antifungal agent, it is used as its nitrate salt in gynaecology for treatment of vulvovaginal infections caused by Candida species, particularly Candida albicans.
A crown ether that is cyclononane in which the carbon atoms at positions 1, 4, and 7 have been replaced by oxygen atoms.
A saturated organic heteromonocyclic parent that is cyclopentadecane in which the carbon atoms at positions 1, 4, 7, 10 and 13 have been replaced by oxygen atoms to give a crown ether.
A phenolate anion that is the conjugate base of catecholate(1-).
An octadecatetraenoic acid containing a conjugated system of  double bonds at positions 9, 11, 13 and 15.
The (9Z,11E,13E,15Z)-isomer of parinaric acid.

An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of equimolar amounts of butaconazole and nitric acid.  An antifungal agent, it is used in gynaecology for treatment of vulvovaginal infections caused by Candida species, particularly Candida albicans.
The all-trans- isomer of parinaric acid.
An octadecadiynoic acid having its triple bonds at positions 10 and 12.
A straight-chain, unsaturated, long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of cis-parinaric acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
A straight-chain, unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of trans-parinaric acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
An icosenoic acid having a cis- double bond at position 9.

Levorphanol in which a hydrogen at position 14 of the morphinan skeleton is substituted by hydroxy and one of the hydrogens of the N-methyl group is substituted by cyclopropyl. A semi-synthetic opioid agonist-antagonist analgesic, it is used as its (S,S)-tartaric acid salt for relief or moderate to severe pain.
A unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of gadoleic acid, formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
An icosenoic acid having a trans- double bond at position 9.
An unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of gadelaidic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group.
An icosenoic acid having a cis- double bond at position 11.
A very long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of gondoic acid, formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
An icosenoyl group derived from (11Z)-icos-11-enoic acid (gondoic acid).
A docosenoic acid having a cis-double bond at position 11.
A straight-chain, monounsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of cetoleic acid.
The (S,S)-tartaric acid salt of butorphanol. It is used for relief or moderate to severe pain.
The L-enantiomer of alaninate.
The L-enantiomer of alaninium.
